                }
            ],
            "ref_spans": [],
            "section": ""
        },
        {
            "text": "Thus, Huang and colleagues 1 should have analysed conjunctival scrapings from both confirmed and suspected 2019nCoV cases during the onset of symptoms. The respiratory tract is probably not the only transmission route for 2019nCoV, and all ophthalmologists examining suspected cases should wear protective eyewear.",
